The seminar was organised in cooperation with the Canada Arab Business Council.

Saeed reviewed social and economic policies adopted by Egypt to confront the negative impact of coronavirus. 

She touched upon investment opportunities in the different sectors, as well as means to support economic relations between Cairo and Ottawa. 

More than 150 Canadian officials, Members of Parliament and board members of giant Canadian firms attended the seminar.

Businessmen wishing to invest in Egypt also took part in the event.  --EgyptToday--